1254	// view (T88). Because the readLoop holds only the PRIMARY's view of a shared socket (one
1255	// reader per socket), the routing that a concentrator needs — a datagram from peer B decoded
1256	// and resequenced under peer B's plane — happens HERE, not by trusting the reader's own view.
1257	//
1258	// Fast path: a socket with a single peer view (the edge/hub, or any socket not shared by a
1259	// second peer) needs no demux — dispatch on the reader's own view, byte-identical to the
1260	// pre-concentrator behaviour. The per-socket view snapshot is read lock-free; a nil/one-entry
1261	// snapshot means "not a shared concentrator socket".
