1346	// maxDemuxSources cap and addr is a NEW source: drop-on-exhaustion (Q26/Q27). A cap-drop NEVER
1347	// evicts an existing binding, so a live peer is never disturbed by a bootstrap flood; only a
1348	// brand-new source's bootstrap is (temporarily) refused, and WG retransmits cover the gap once
1349	// a slot frees (e.g. a dead peer's teardown). Re-pointing or re-affirming an already-present
1350	// source does not grow the map and is therefore never blocked by the cap.
